news.title: Goa: Occupancy certificate withheld for Calapur project over environmental concerns
news.para: The HC told the deputy solicitor general of India to take instructions on the aspect of the relaxation of the setback for the project, as the petitioner’s counsel, Rohit Bras de Sa, told the HC that only central govt is empowered to grant such a relaxation.

news.title: Innov8 launches two lakh sq ft flexible spaces in Mumbai and Navi Mumbai
news.para: Q Parc - is located along the Thane-Belapur Road in Ghansoli with a total seating capacity of 1,500 while Innov8 Zion – the Andheri center has a total seating capacity of 1,500.

news.title: Madhu Mantena acquires three apartments for Rs 25.75 crore in Mumbai’s Juhu
news.para: Madhu Mantena’s productions include Ghajini (2008), Queen (2015), Masaan and many more.

news.title: Noida: YEIDA completes 1,400 registries for industrial plots
news.para: The increasing interest in completing registries has been driven by the development of the upcoming Noida International Airport, which has significantly boosted the region's appeal.

news.title: Second phase of Mumbai metro-III to be operational by May 2025: Maharashtra CM
news.para: PM Narendra Modi inaugurated the Aarey–BKC first phase of the underground Metro 3 in Oct, while also launching several other infrastructure projects in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region.

news.title: World Bank approves $800 million loan for development of Amaravati
news.para: Situated in a well-connected region along India's east coast, Amaravati will be part of a broader metropolitan region that includes two cities, Vijayawada and Guntur.

news.title: Mizoram government collects over Rs 8 crore from stamp, land registration fees
news.para: In February, the state assembly passed the Indian Stamp (Mizoram Amendment) Bill, 2024, which seeks to hike stamp duty from 1 per cent to 3 per cent of the property.

news.title: NGT asks environment ministry to inspect Okhla Bird Sanctuary for illegal construction
news.para: ​​The green body was hearing a plea claiming that the divisional forest officer (DFO) concerned was constructing illegal permanent structures inside the sanctuary, which was located on the Yamuna River floodplain.

news.title: Bombay HC dismisses plea against Adani group's Dharavi redevelopment tender
news.para: The petition was filed by a private firm that had contested the award, which followed the cancellation of a previous tender in 2019.

news.title: Developers urge government to reconsider proposal to bring FSI, additional FSI under GST
news.para: Realty developers’ body CREDAI has written to the finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman urging a review of the proposal as the move would result in a substantial incremental impact on project costs, pushing housing prices up by around 10% across various property markets of the country.

news.title: Gurugram civic body aims to clear 10,000 tonnes of C&D waste daily
news.para: In a review meeting of the Solid Waste Environment Exigency Programme (SWEEP), divisional commissioner RC Bidhan told MCG officials ensure registration of vehicles collecting C&D waste area-wise and that their rates be fixed.

news.title: Existing home sales in USA surge 4.8% in November 2024
news.para: Existing home sales rose 4.8% last month, from October, to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 4.15 million, the National Association of Realtors said Thursday.

news.title: Chinese banks in several cities raise mortgage rates as profits shrink: Reports
news.para: Some commercial banks in cities such as Guangzhou, Qingdao and Nanjing have raised first-home mortgage rates by 5 basis points (bps) to 20 bps since November, to as high as 3.1%, the official Beijng Daily, among other media, reported.

news.title: HYDRAA won’t encroach on GHMC's powers: Telangana government
news.para: The govt also amended the Telangana municipalities and Telangana Panchayat Raj Act, enabling the enhancement of the reservations in the local bodies.

news.title: NGT seeks collector’s reply on illegal dumping of construction debris in Vasai
news.para: The petitioner approached the NGT after his complaints to the Vasai Virar City Municipal Corporation (VVCMC) did not result in "any positive action".

news.title: Pune civic body recovers 34 crore in property tax from defaulters
news.para: "Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) sent recovery notices to these defaulters. But the owners did not pay their dues and so, were targeted in this special drive," said Madhav Jagtap, head of PMC's property tax department.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body imposes time restrictions on construction work
news.para: Building constructions will now be allowed from 7am to 10pm, Singh told TOI on the sidelines of an event organised by real estate body Naredco.

news.title: BBMP to demolish 29 buildings in Bengaluru south zone
news.para: The action follows a directive from Vinoth Priya R, BBMP south zone commissioner, to crack down on unauthorised constructions.

news.title: Hyderabad: HYDRAA razes illegal structures in residential complex in Manikonda
news.para: Residents of 38 flats had raised concerns with HYDRAA about the misuse of residential permissions for commercial purposes on the ground floor, a complaint they had first reported to the Narsingi police station three years ago.

news.title: Ventive Hospitality raises Rs 719.55 crore from 26 anchor investors ahead of IPO
news.para: Out of the total allocation of 1,11,90,513 equity shares to the anchor investors, 48,21,122 equity shares(i.e. 43.08% of the total allocation to anchor investors) were allocated to four domestic mutual funds through a total of eight schemes.
